definition.value: an adverse event that displays an outcome of ulcer.
a musculoskeletal and connective tissue AE that displays an outcome of fistula, a permanent abnormal passageway between two organs in the body or between an organ and the exterior of the body.
an adverse event that displays an outcome of an sclerosis, the stiffening of a structure, usually caused by a replacement of the normal organ-specific tissue with connective tissue.
a crying abnormal AE that has an outcome of abnormal inconsolable crying in a patient
a crying abnormal AE that has an outcome of abnormal unusual high-pitched crying in a patient
a crying abnormal AE that has an outcome of abnormal prolonged crying in a patient
a decreased heart rate AE that results in a resting heart rate of under 60 beats per minutes (BPM).

definition.value: an adverse event that displays a disorder associated with child birth, newborn infant, or an infant.
a bupropion-induced adverse event that is induced by aplenzin administration
an adverse event that occurs in the site of a medical intervention (e.g., vaccination injection site).
A pregnancy, neonatal and perinatal AE that displays a disorder associated with newborn infant or an infant.
A pregnancy, neonatal and perinatal AE that displays a disorder associated with childbirth
a vascular disorder AE that affects the artery
an artery disorder AE that is characterized by a narrowing of the blood vessels outside of the heart.
an autoimmune disease AE that shows a symptom of dry red patches on the skin.
a distal sensory neuropathy AE characterized by an increase in degree (cumulative)
a behavior and neurological AE that has an outcome of stress in a patient
an abscess AE that has an outcome of a pocket of infected fluid and pus located inside the abdominal cavity
a discomfort AE that has an outcome of a stomach ache
a sensory capability AE that results in a sensation of elevated abdominal pressure and volume
a sepsis AE that has an outcome of sepsis in the abdominal area
an abdominal abscess AE that has an outcome of a collection of pus in the abdominal wall, causes inflammation
a behavioral and neurological AE that results in odd dreams

an abortion AE that results in a miscarriage
a skin AE that is characterized by pimples generally on the face, chest and back, caused by clogging of the pores

label.value: activated partial thromboplastin time prolonged AE

definition.value: a hematopoietic system AE that has an outcome of a prolonged time taken for blood to clot. The partial thromboplastin time (PTT) is a blood test that looks at how long it takes for blood to clot. PTT measures the efficacy of the comon coagulation pathways and helps tell if bleeding or clotting problems exist.

label.value: acute graft versus host disease in intestine AE

definition.value: a digestive system AE that has an outcome of a complication during stem cell or bone marrow transplant in which the newly transplanted donor cells in the intestine attack the transplant recipient's body

label.value: acute graft versus host disease in skin AE

definition.value: a skin AE that has an outcome of a complication during stem cell or bone marrow transplant in which the newly transplanted donor cells in the skin attack the transplant recipient's body

an acute myeloid leukemia AE that shows an recurrence of acute myeloid leukemia
a lung disorder AE that has the outcome fluid accumulation in the air spaces and parenchyma of the lungs with rapid onset

a lung disorder AE that has an outcome of a condition in which not enough oxygen passes from the lungs into the blood, with rapid onset

a reproductive system AE that results in the thickening of the walls of the uterus. This ccurs when endometrial tissue, which normally lines the uterus, moves into the outer muscular walls of the uterus.
a viral infection that occurs in the respiratory system and has an outcome of viral infection by nonenveloped icosahedral viruses causing illness in the respiratory system

an endocrine system AE that results in the suppression of the functions of the adrenal glands
